{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"artsy-chain-hold","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n1. Close a work ticket with the completion-verification gate enabled (verify.require_completion_verification_for_close=true).\n2. For certain inputs (observed deterministically on ticket b593, a tiny pyproject metadata diff), the verify-step model emits its structured output as a top-level JSON **array** (a bare list of findings) rather than the completion_verdict **object**.\n3. src/rebar/llm/structured.py validate_to() raises StructuredOutputError('structured output must be a JSON object, got list'); the workflow step 'decide@then/verify' fails and the close is blocked fail-closed.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: verifier tolerates/normalizes a single-verdict wrapped in a list (or the verify prompt/schema forces an object), producing a PASS/FAIL verdict.\n- Actual: deterministic parse failure (5/5 attempts); the ticket cannot earn a signed completion attestation and must be --force-closed (left uncertified).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] tolerant_parse/validate_to in src/rebar/llm/structured.py robustly handles a top-level array carrying one verdict object (unwrap), OR the completion verify step constrains output to an object.\n- [ ] A regression test reproduces the 'got list' input and asserts a verdict is produced.\n- [ ] Closing a previously-affected ticket earns a signed completion-verifier PASS.","id":"2ede-2459-90ce-4b19","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"completion-verifier: top-level JSON array from verify model fails to parse (validate_to 'got list')"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783216528314278001,"uuid":"46ef2013-ec6c-4ca8-a89b-1a970227b1fe"}